headline: Kimberly-Clark Q4 Earnings Top Estimates, Organic Sales Up 2.1%
summary: KMB beats fourth-quarter estimates as organic sales rose 2.1%, even as revenues dip from exiting its U.S. private-label diaper business.

headline: Kimberly-Clark Posts Higher Profit Ahead of Kenvue Vote
summary: Kimberly-Clark reported a higher profit in its latest quarter just days before shareholders vote on its plan to buy Kenvue, a deal designed to create a global health-and-wellness giant.
